title: Osho_From Death to Deathlessness #01.mp4
description:
Questions and answers to disciples in Rajneeshpuram, 1985
On the begininnig and on the end is music and dance with Bhagwan

From Death to Deathlessness,
Chapter #1
Chapter title: The man of compassion has to lie
2 August 1985 am in Rajneeshmandir
Length: 	91 mins

Question 1
BELOVED OSHO,
YOU SAID THAT YOU LIE OUT OF COMPASSION, AND WE, YOUR SANNYASINS, CAN UNDERSTAND WHAT YOU ARE SAYING. BUT CAN THE OUTSIDE WORLD EVER UNDERSTAND? WON'T IT CREATE MORE MISUNDERSTANDING ABOUT YOU, ABOUT RAJNEESHISM, ABOUT YOUR SANNYASINS? PLEASE COMMENT.

Compassion knows no conditions. It can do anything, it knows no right and no wrong. Compassion can lie to help you. In fact, in your sleep you can only understand lies, you cannot understand the truth
